

Practical of Cross Join
=========================




1) In the Left Table we Have 3 Records & In the Right Table we Have 3 Records. If we Use Cross Join It will Try to Combine Each Record On the Left Table with Each Record On The Right Table. 

That Will be 3x3= 9 (As Shown Below)


SELECT p.*,c.* FROM product p JOIN color c;

+------------+--------------+----------+------------+
| product_id | product_name | color_id | color_name |
+------------+--------------+----------+------------+
|          3 | Mug          |        1 | Red        |
|          2 | Hoodie       |        1 | Red        |
|          1 | T-shirt      |        1 | Red        |
|          3 | Mug          |        2 | Blue       |
|          2 | Hoodie       |        2 | Blue       |
|          1 | T-shirt      |        2 | Blue       |
|          3 | Mug          |        3 | Green      |
|          2 | Hoodie       |        3 | Green      |
|          1 | T-shirt      |        3 | Green      |
+------------+--------------+----------+------------+






2) Below is the Count of the Records which Cross Join is Providing

SELECT COUNT(*) FROM product p JOIN color c;

+----------+
| COUNT(*) |
+----------+
|        9 |
+----------+









