3) In the Below Query we have Found the 3 States Which has Received Maximum Number of Orders 


SELECT c.customer_state, COUNT(*) AS num_of_orders 
FROM customers c 
INNER JOIN orders o ON o.order_customer_id = c.customer_id 
GROUP BY c.customer_state 
ORDER BY num_of_orders DESC
LIMIT 3;

+----------------+---------------+
| customer_state | num_of_orders |
+----------------+---------------+
| PR             |         26510 |
| CA             |         11051 |
| NY             |          4331 |
+----------------+---------------+









4) Find Top 5 Customers With Maximum Orders in Closed Status

SELECT order_customer_id, COUNT(*) AS num_of_orders 
FROM orders 
WHERE order_status = 'CLOSED' 
GROUP BY order_customer_id 
ORDER BY num_of_orders DESC 
LIMIT 5; 

